comment: Multi zone VAV AHU economizer enable/disable switch

parameters.name: use_enthalpy
parameters.comment: Set to true to evaluate outdoor air (OA) enthalpy in addition to temperature

parameters.name: delTOutHis
parameters.comment: Delta between the temperature hysteresis high and low limit

parameters.name: delEntHis
parameters.comment: Delta between the enthalpy hysteresis high and low limits

parameters.name: retDamFulOpeTim
parameters.comment:
Time period to keep RA damper fully open before releasing it for minimum outdoor airflow control
    at disable to avoid pressure fluctuations

parameters.name: disDel
parameters.comment: Short time delay before closing the OA damper at disable to avoid pressure fluctuations

models.name: truFalHol
models.comment: Economizer should not be enabled or disabled within 10 minutes of change

models.name: andEnaDis
models.comment: Check freeze protection stage and zone state

inputs.name: TOutCut
inputs.comment: OA temperature high limit cutoff. For differential dry bulb temperature condition use return air temperature measurement

inputs.name: hOutCut
inputs.comment: OA enthalpy high limit cutoff. For differential enthalpy use return air enthalpy measurement

inputs.name: uOutDam_min
inputs.comment: Minimum outdoor air damper position, output from damper position limits sequence

inputs.name: uOutDam_max
inputs.comment: Maximum outdoor air damper position, output from damper position limits sequence

inputs.name: uRetDam_max
inputs.comment: Maximum return air damper position, output from damper position limits sequence

inputs.name: uRetDam_min
inputs.comment: Minimum return air damper position, output from damper position limits sequence

inputs.name: uRetDamPhy_max
inputs.comment: Physical maximum return air damper position, output from damper position limits sequence

models.name: sub2
models.comment: Add block determines difference between hOut and hOutCut

models.name: sub1
models.comment: Add block determines difference between TOut and TOutCut

models.name: hysOutTem
models.comment: Outdoor air temperature hysteresis for both fixed and differential dry bulb temperature cutoff conditions

models.name: hysOutEnt
models.comment: Outdoor air enthalpy hysteresis for both fixed and differential enthalpy cutoff conditions

models.name: outDamSwitch
models.comment: Set maximum OA damper position to minimum at disable (after a given time delay)

models.name: retDamSwitch
models.comment: Set minimum RA damper position to maximum at disable

models.name: maxRetDamSwitch
models.comment: Keep maximum RA damper position at physical maximum for a short time period after disable signal

models.name: minRetDamSwitch
models.comment: Keep minimum RA damper position at physical maximum for a short time period after disable

models.name: not2
models.comment: Logical not that starts the timer at disable signal

models.name: and2
models.comment: Logical and

models.name: and1
models.comment: Check supply fan status

models.name: and3
models.comment: Check if delay time has been passed after economizer being disabled

models.name: intEqu
models.comment: Logical block to check if the freeze protection is deactivated

models.name: delOutDamOsc
models.comment: Small delay before closing the outdoor air damper to avoid pressure fluctuations

models.name: delRetDam
models.comment: Keep return damper open to its physical maximum for a short period of time before closing the outdoor air damper and resuming the maximum return air damper position, per G36 Part N7

models.name: not1
models.comment: Logical not

models.name: conInt
models.comment: Integer constant, stage 0

models.name: entSubst1
models.comment: Deactivates outdoor air enthalpy condition if there is no enthalpy sensor

models.name: or2
models.comment: Check if either the temperature or the enthalpy condition is satisfied

info:
This is a multi zone VAV AHU economizer enable/disable sequence based on the Section 5.16.7 of the ASHRAE Guideline 36, May 2020. Additional conditions included in the sequence are: freeze protection (freeze protection stage 0-3, see Section 5.16.12), supply fan status (on or off, see Section 5.16.5).

The economizer is disabled whenever the outdoor air conditions exceed the economizer high limit setpoint. This sequence allows for all device types listed in ASHRAE 90.1-2013 and Title 24-2013.

In addition, the economizer gets disabled without a delay whenever any of the following is true:

  • The supply fan is off (u1SupFan = false),
  • the freeze protection stage Buildings.Controls.OBC.ASHRAE.G36.Types.FreezeProtectionStages is not stage0.

The following state machine chart illustrates the transitions between enabling and disabling:

After the disable signal is activated, the following procedure is applied, in order to prevent pressure fluctuations in the HVAC system:

  • The return damper gets fully opened (yRetDam_max = uRetDamPhy_max and yRetDam_min = uRetDamPhy_max) for retDamFulOpeTim time period, after which the return damper gets released to its minimum outdoor airflow control position (yRetDam_max = uRetDam_max and yRetDam_min = uRetDam_max).
  • The outdoor air damper is closed to its minimum outoor airflow control limit (yOutDam_max = uOutDam_min) after a disDel time delay.
